The Sharon region was almost uninhabited by the Jewish population until 1924. However, then a significant part (about 20%) of the emigrants of the second half of the 1920s settled in the Sharon region. On September 8, 1928, 1400 dunams of land were bought from the Arab sheikh Hamdan for 5600 lira. Netanya was founded on February 18, 1929 by immigrants from Eastern Europe as an agricultural settlement - moshav. On October 2, 1932, it received the official status of a village, on December 3, 1948 - a city.